definition:
A woman living at the time before the Flood, first mentioned at Gen.26.34; 
 daughter of: Elon (H0356); married to Esau (H6215); 
 mother of: Eliphaz (H0464); also called Basemath (KJV: Bashemath) at Gen.26.34; 
Another name of a.dah (עָדָה "Adah" H5711H)
 § Bashemath or Basmath = "spice"
1) Hittite wife of Esau, daughter of Ishmael, sister of Nebaioth
2) daughter of Solomon, wife of Ahimaaz, one of Solomon's commissariat officers
